annotationA: Hold'em is predicted to be a single-strand DNA binding protein based on the presence of three Oligosaccharide-Binding (OB) folds. It is involved in making meiotic crossovers and in some DNA repair process
annotationB: Replication factor C 38kD subunit, isoform A; DNA clamp loader activity; ATPase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: DNA replication; neurogenesis
